# ChartIQ AWS Infrastructure

Infrastructure-as-code for deploying CloudFront distributions with S3 origins using a single-state architecture.

## Overview

Manages complete CloudFront distributions with all required resources:
- CloudFront Distributions (OAC-secured)
- S3 Buckets (versioned, encrypted)
- Lambda@Edge Functions (headers, auth, SPA)
- Route53 DNS Records
- Project Logging Buckets

**Single-State Architecture:** All resources managed together per environment - no circular dependencies, simplified deployment.

## Quick Start

### 1. Configure Distribution

Edit `config/{environment}/distributions.yaml`:

```yaml
aws_account_id: "123456789012"
route53_zone_id: "Z1234567890ABC"

distributions:
  - name: my-app
    enabled: true
    domain: my-app.example.com
    s3_bucket: my-app-bucket
    certificate_arn: arn:aws:acm:us-east-1:123456789012:certificate/xxx
    
    cloudfront:
      enable_spa_handling: true
      price_class: PriceClass_100
    
    tags:
      AppID: ASP0002996
      Owner: team@example.com
```

### 2. Deploy

**Via GitHub (Recommended):**
```bash
# In PR comment:
.deploy dev          # Deploy to dev
.deploy staging      # Deploy to staging
.deploy prod         # Deploy to prod
```

**Manual:**
```bash
cd environments/dev
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply
```

## Repository Structure

```
chartiq-app-aws-infra/
├── config/                    # YAML configuration files
│   ├── dev/
│   ├── staging/
│   └── prod/
├── environments/              # Terraform code (single state per env)
│   ├── dev/
│   ├── staging/
│   └── prod/
├── modules/
│   └── cloudfront-distribution/
└── docs/                      # Detailed documentation
    ├── ARCHITECTURE.md
    ├── CONFIGURATION.md
    └── DEPLOYMENT.md
```

## Deployment Methods

| Environment | Method | Approval Required |
|-------------|--------|-------------------|
| dev | Auto-deploy on merge or `.deploy dev` | No |
| staging | `.deploy staging` in PR | 1 approval |
| prod | `.deploy prod` in PR | 2 approvals |

## Key Features

- **Single Terraform State:** All resources managed together
- **No Circular Dependencies:** Uses data sources for lazy evaluation
- **Blueprint Modules:** S3 bucket and project-logging modules from terraform__foundation
- **Branch Deploy:** Safe deployments from PR comments
- **OIDC Authentication:** GitHub Actions uses role-based access

## Documentation

- [ARCHITECTURE.md](docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) - Technical architecture and single-state approach
- [CONFIGURATION.md](docs/CONFIGURATION.md) - Full configuration reference
- [DEPLOYMENT.md](docs/DEPLOYMENT.md) - Deployment procedures and troubleshooting

## Security

- S3 buckets: Public access blocked, encryption enabled
- CloudFront: Origin Access Control (OAC), HTTPS enforced
- State: Encrypted in S3 with lockfile support
- CI/CD: OIDC authentication, no long-term credentials

