# CloudFront Distribution Module

This module creates a complete CloudFront distribution with all required dependencies.

## Features

- CloudFront distribution with Origin Access Control (OAC)
- Lambda@Edge functions for headers, authentication, and SPA handling
- Route53 DNS records
- IAM roles and policies
- CloudWatch log groups

## Usage

```hcl
module "cloudfront_distribution" {
  source = "../../modules/cloudfront-distribution"

  name                = "my-app"
  domain              = "my-app.example.com"
  zone_id             = "Z1234567890ABC"
  certificate_arn     = "arn:aws:acm:us-east-1:123456789012:certificate/xxx"
  log_bucket          = "logs-bucket"
  s3_bucket_regional_domain_name = "my-bucket.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com"

  # Optional
  enable_spa_handling = true
  oidc_client_id      = "my-client-id"
  
  tags = {
    Environment = "dev"
    Project     = "chartiq"
  }
}
```

## Requirements

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| terraform | >= 1.0 |
| aws | >= 6.0, < 7 |

## Inputs

See [variables.tf](variables.tf) for all available inputs.

## Outputs

See [outputs.tf](outputs.tf) for all available outputs.

